We are seeking a highly skilled Senior PyTorch Engineer (Distributed Training) to join our AI/ML team. The ideal candidate will have strong hands-on expertise in PyTorch Core, PyTorch Lightning, and Distributed Data Parallel (DDP) to build scalable multi-GPU and multi-node deep learning systems.

You will work on designing and training large-scale deep learning models powering high-impact, production-grade AI systems serving millions of users.

Key Responsibilities

Design, develop, and train advanced deep learning models using PyTorch
Implement scalable training pipelines using PyTorch Lightning
Build and optimize Distributed Data Parallel (DDP) workflows
Enable efficient multi-GPU and multi-node training
Optimize training performance (memory usage, GPU utilization, throughput)
Build custom datasets, data loaders, and preprocessing pipelines
Implement and tune loss functions, optimizers, and learning rate schedulers
Debug gradient flow issues, numerical instabilities, and bottlenecks
Collaborate with Data Scientists, Research Engineers, and Platform teams
Ensure modular, production-ready, and scalable code architecture
Contribute to model validation, experiment tracking, and reproducibility
